beyond the stalled revolution reinvigorating gender equality in the twenty first century beyond the stalled revolution reinvigorating gender equality in the twenty first century facebook twitter email print add to calendar the clayman institute invites you to come and be part of the conversation to reinvigorate the gender revolution our panel of experts will include professor laura l carstensen professor estelle b freedman professor deborah l rhode and professor myra h strober the panel will be moderated by the new director of the clayman institute professor shelley correll the panel will provide new insights from many perspectives and experiences into the barriers to women's advancement and propose workable solutions to advancing gender equality when thursday november 4 2010 4 15 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where levinthall hall stanford humanities center map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags humanities environment public service international conference symposium engineering sponsor clayman institute for gender research contact 725 0373 ann enthoven stanford edu admission free and open to all permalink http events stanford edu events 251 25175 more info last modified november 4 2010
